# 📝 Test Plan: Shopping Cart Functionality

## 📌 **Objective:**
Ensure that the shopping cart functionality works correctly, allowing users to add, remove, and manage items before checkout.

## 📌 **Scope:**
- Adding items to the cart
- Removing items from the cart
- Updating item quantities
- Validating cart calculations (subtotal, taxes, total price)
- Handling cart persistence across sessions

## 📌 **Test Approach:**
- Functional testing for core shopping cart actions
- UI testing to ensure a user-friendly experience
- Negative testing (e.g., adding invalid quantities)
- Database validation for cart updates

## 📌 **Test Cases:**

| Test ID  | Test Case Name                 | Description |
|----------|--------------------------------|-------------|
| TC-001   | Adding Items to the Cart      | Verify that users can add items to the shopping cart successfully. |
| TC-002   | Removing Items from the Cart  | Ensure users can remove items from their cart. |
| TC-003   | Updating Item Quantity        | Validate that changing the quantity of items updates the subtotal correctly. |
| TC-004   | Validating Cart Persistence   | Ensure that items remain in the cart after refreshing the page. |
| TC-005   | Empty Cart Message            | Confirm that an empty cart displays an appropriate message. |
| TC-006   | Applying Discount Codes       | Verify that users can apply valid discount codes. |
| TC-007   | Handling Expired Discount Codes | Ensure expired discount codes display an appropriate error. |
| TC-008   | Checking Out Successfully     | Validate that users can complete checkout successfully. |
| TC-009   | Payment Failure Handling      | Confirm that users are notified if a payment fails. |
| TC-010   | Multi-Device Cart Persistence | Ensure cart contents are maintained when switching devices. |

## 📌 **Test Environment:**
- Browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari
- OS: Windows, macOS, Android, iOS
- Database: MySQL/PostgreSQL

## 📌 **Pass/Fail Criteria:**
- Pass: Shopping cart behaves as expected for all test cases.
- Fail: Items are not added, removed, or updated correctly.

## 📌 **Risks & Assumptions:**
- Session management must be working correctly.
- Cart data must be stored properly in the database.